description.narrative: In 2019, the Country Office supported the implementation of basic emergency obstetrical and neonatal care (BEmONC), including post-partum hemorrhage management with uterine balloon tamponade (UBT), newborn resuscitation and KMC. These interventions targeted a population of 153,841 pregnant women and mothers and 146,265 newborns in Abidjan and in 13 health districts. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/12/2019
